title: The Latest: Royals strike first for 2-0 lead in ALCS (Yahoo Sports)
text: Posts: 54,315 The Latest: Royals strike first for 2-0 lead in ALCS (Yahoo Sports) The Royals are playing from ahead in the postseason for a change. Alcides Escobar hit an RBI double and Lorenzo Cain a run-scoring single to give Kansas City a 2-0 lead over the Toronto Blue Jays after three innings in Game 1. Escobar already has a pair of doubles off Marco Estrada, who got the starting nod for Toronto over former Cy Young winner and Game 2 starter David Price.
